I am incredibly sad and heartbroken over the loss of Jay Briscoe. Words can not describe the kindness that he and his family has shown mine. Jay was one of the toughest men I have ever met but he had a way of making everyone feel special that got to work with him. My condolences go to his family and friends. This loss is too much. Jay was a pillar in the wrestling community as he was the definition of a locker room leader and good human being. Jay always asked about my family, he and his wife came to our wedding, and when Jay gave you a hug he meant it. Thank you for the memories and your friendship. You will be missed. #ripjaybriscoe @ringofhonor

Today I am getting thyroid surgery to remove half my thyroid which includes a nodule. I’ve been have symptoms for the past 2 and a half years. Heart racing, trouble with weight loss, skin changes, exhaustion, mood changes, sore throat, anxiety, period changes, raspy voice, trouble swallowing, brain fog, calcium deficiency, amongst others. But, with having 2 kids, the Pandemic, and multiple times being fired I just didn’t have the time to really focus on it. Now, my doctor has told me that there are abnormal cells which could turn cancerous and a possibility of causing afib, which is a heart condition. So, with the full support of @aew, it’s time. Thank you to @tonyrkhan, Megha, and CD for the support!! And of course thank you to my wonderful husband @therealmichaelbennett and my amazing mother for helping us through this time!! Recovery is supposed to be about 2 weeks for the incision and about a year for the hormones to balance. I can work after 2 weeks with no restrictions. I will keep you all posted… 

Here is a photo pre-thyroid surgery scar. Hahaha… 

#thyroidsurgeryscar #thyroidproblems #thyroidawarenessmonth #thyroidcancerawareness #thyroidissues

Mike and I came across this song early in our relationship and it became an anthem for what we didn’t want. The sarcasm in this song is about not doing things the way people say you should. We don’t live in a little box, we did not do things the way people said we should, we have crazy jobs, and 2 young children. We have been on the road 8 out of the last 11 days. We were on wrestling programming @aew Dark, Dynamite. @ringofhonor, and Rampage and episode 29 of @womenswrestlingarmy debuted which I helped produce. We are blessed. We are grateful. We pray. We try to be the best parents. We try to be good people. But, we also try to just focus on our path. @therealmichaelbennett @freddiemoonbennett @carvermarsbennett

About a year ago, I questioned if maybe it was time to be done with wrestling. @ringofhonor had closed, we were out of a job and in a lot of ways we were out of having the energy to fight in this industry. One year later we were on @aew and @ringofhonor 4x this week!!! Plus, a brand new episode of Women’s Wrestling Army is on @prowtv and on BrandArmy.com/womenswrestlingarmy #godisgood

Happy International Women’s Day!!! I am so incredibly grateful to be able to work with such talented individuals!! 

I have been tested a lot this week with many different facets in my life. There are people and outside forces fighting against me. I know it. I can feel it. That’s okay. I forgive you. I’ve been doing this at a high level for a long time and I’d rather have a legacy of helping people than hurting people. Thank you for the struggle because it has made me strong. I want to give opportunities for women in the industry, that is my career goal. I want to be an example for good, that is for my children. 

Other than that, I just want to work. And I want to create a place for those that want to JUST work. That freaks people out. My husband always tells me I frighten people with my honesty. I am on a mission. I will not sacrifice my soul to gain power. I will not apologize for that. But, I will say thank you to those that have given me the opportunity to grow and to perform. I pray that I learn all the lessons I can from this current situation. I put my faith in God. I trust this process and at the end of the day hell hath no fury like a woman scorn. Haha… this is me saying bring it. And someday maybe we can laugh about it. #internationalwomensday #moreopportunitiesmeanmoreopportunities @womenswrestlingarmy

Good morning to everyone that hates me… I can’t wait to hang out on your TV so you have to look at the person actively changing the industry. Actively changing perceptions about age, gender, and the power or lack there is of women in this industry. I’ve been in the business of creating opportunities since 2004. I don’t wrestle. I manage. And because of that people hate me but Paul Heyman does it and gets praised. I hate the way wrestling portrays women in this industry so rather than just bitch about it, I created @womenswrestlingarmy with Bobby Cruise and what do I get more hate. I don’t do it for you. I do it for my family and for the girls. For my daughter, for when she screams about what she wants at 5 years old I will tell her scream louder because there are people in this world that will try to diminish you because of your gender. So stand up, scream loud, and never give in. @womenswrestlingarmy @aew @ringofhonor

So I’m going to do this Birthday post in pieces. Because after 12 years there is a lot of life to cover. When I met Mike he had 2 pairs of shoes and a beat up pair of wrestling boots. He loved country music and simple foods. No sauce not even ketchup. He was shy and nice to a fault. Mike was supposed to be just a fun few dates. But, here we are 12 years later. Every photo on this reel means something to Mike or myself. We built a friendship in those first 3 years before we got married full of trips to Vegas, a foreclosure on my house in LA, working together in @ringofhonor, and having absolutely not a dollar between us. We had fun, we laughed, and we built a foundation that gets us through even NOW. I can not believe how much you’ve grown. I loved this baby you but I love you so much more now!! Happy Birthday Part 1. @therealmichaelbennett

Happy Birthday Part 2. Our vows were don’t say it, prove it with what you do. During these years you were addicted to pain killers, numbing so many things that I loved about you. You sat in our living room in Providence stuck in your own way. Stuck in your ways. I blamed myself for so long for not seeing the addiction. But, I wouldn’t trade those tears for nothing because they brought me here. They brought us here. @therealmichaelbennett

Part 3. Happy Birthday I’m glad you are still alive. BUT, You probably should have died with the shit you were putting in your body… I probably should have left you with the hell you put me through. But I am a stubborn Midwest bitch that doesn’t believe in divorce. 2 weeks after you started your recovery I found out I was pregnant. I was so scared. But, that was the turning point, that was the beginning of the breaking down to build back up. Freddie was born about 9 months later and a few days after that you were at Wrestlemania. What a life… what a beautiful crazy life…

Part 4 Happy Birthday!! Navigating parenthood, postpartum depression and recovery was complicated. Putting it lightly. There were times I thought it would never get easier. And then one baby turned into 2 when we had Carver in 2020. I thought we would be tired forever and just when things started to get a little easier we got fired. And then there was a pandemic and a lockdown. Those countless hours with a newborn and a 2 year old seemed like days. The days ran into months. And we just held each other and to our sanity as we searched for jobs and spent our savings. Waiting for the pandemic to be over… but no matter what was thrown as us I knew we would figure it out, fight it out together. Because there is always hope… @therealmichaelbennett

Part 5 Happy Birthday Mike Post!!! We went from losing our jobs in WWE to losing our jobs in ROH to going to Impact to now being back in @ringofhonor. Sometimes, I ask myself how? How is our lives so full? When we are starting from 0 again after almost 3 years of draining everything we had. But, somehow I am still not discouraged and I’m still grateful. I’m actually more grateful than I have ever been. We are all healthy and in a company I feel we can retire in. I’m excited for the future and I’m excited for the many many birthdays to come. Thank you for this beautiful life. We are Blessed to have such beautiful, empathetic, brilliant, loving children. I love you to the Moon and Mars and back… @therealmichaelbennett #BGSD

I don’t make the rules: but you have to learn the rules of the game. And then, you have to play better than anyone else. Diva, First Lady, Knockout, Manager, Mother, CEO, Agent of Change… 7 well established characters, each with the accolades, education, and experience to back it up. Each company had a flavor. Each story a unique impetus. Every management style an appetite to nourish. It’s a game or a fight, a strategy or a political mind fuck, a manipulation or a manifesto. Doesn’t matter the method or the modus operandi. The why is all that matters. I love to help the next generation and I need to feed my family. We as humans are not one phenomenon and as a 41 year old mother, the last thing I am is a sheep mewing into that last good night. What I am is a lioness blending into the talentless brush gathering a pack, an ARMY to find victory in an endless, relentless hunt for success.

10 kids, 2 grandmas, my mom and dad, 4 cousins, 2 aunts, 2 uncles, my brother, sister in law, mike and myself. Christmas is for family. Watching it grow from when I was little to now is incredible. Family coming and going, stretching and contracting, the stories, the laughter, the poker, the roles everyone takes on, we don’t talk politics, or religion. We talk family and children. What is everyone up to and usually the children playing fills any silence. This wasn’t everyone but this is a good example of our Christmas chaos. Forever grateful for the loud house, in a quiet town where family is everything.
